  <li><strong>Palm branches:</strong> Three of the four Gospel accounts mention the crowd getting some kind of branch and spreading those branches on the road in front of Jesus. The writers of Matthew and Mark write â€œbranches from the treesâ€ and â€œbranches that they had cut in the fields,â€ respectively, while Johnâ€™s Gospel specifically mentions â€œbranches of palm trees.â€ Johnâ€™s specific designation of palm trees and the recurring scene across the Gospels of people in the crowd taking branches and laying them on the path before Jesus has led to the incorperation of palm branches into Palm Sunday, and into the name of Palm Sunday itself.</li>
